Q1. What is HTML and why do we use it?

Simple: HTML ek markup language hai jo web pages create karne ke liye use hoti hai.

Professional:
HTML (HyperText Markup Language) is the standard language for creating web pages. It structures the content, defines layout, and works with CSS and JavaScript to build interactive web applications.

Q2. What is the basic structure of an HTML document?
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <title>Document</title>
  </head>
  <body>
    <h1>Hello, World!</h1>
  </body>
</html>

Explanation:

<!DOCTYPE html>: HTML5 document type

<html>: Root tag

<head>: Metadata and linking assets

<body>: Visible content

Q3. What are semantic tags? Why are they important?

Answer:
Semantic tags convey meaning to the browser and other developers. They improve readability and SEO.
Examples:

<header> â†’ Header content

<nav> â†’ Navigation

<main> â†’ Main content

<article> â†’ Independent content

<footer> â†’ Footer

Q4. What are self-closing or void tags in HTML? Give examples.

Answer:
Void tags do not need a closing tag and cannot contain content.
Examples: <br>, <hr>, <img>, <input>, <meta>

Q5. How can you embed audio and video in HTML?

Answer:
Using <audio> and <video> tags.

Example:
<audio controls>
  <source src="audio.mp3" type="audio/mpeg">
</audio>

<video width="400" controls>
  <source src="video.mp4" type="video/mp4">
</video>


ðŸŽ¤ Q6. What's the difference between <div> and <section>?

<div> is a non-semantic container used for grouping content for styling/layout.

<section> is a semantic tag used for meaningful grouping of related content.

